# Code Review & Quality — Five-Axis Review

## Correctness
- Does it match spec? Edge cases handled? Error paths covered? Tests adequate?

## Readability & Simplicity
- Descriptive names? Straightforward control flow? Could be fewer lines? No dead code?

## Architecture
- Follows existing patterns? Clean module boundaries? Proper dependency direction?

## Security
- Input validated? Secrets out of code? SQL parameterized? External data untrusted?

## Performance
- No N+1 queries? No unbounded loops? Async where needed? Pagination present?

## Additional Rules

- **Change sizing:** ~100 lines good, ~300 acceptable, ~1000 too large (split it)
- **Categorize findings:** Critical (blocks merge), Required (no prefix), Nit (optional), FYI (informational)
- Use `logger` not `print()` in source code
- Avoid bare `except:` — use `except Exception:` at minimum
- After changes, check for orphaned/dead code
- Before adding dependencies: check existing stack, size, maintenance, license, vulnerabilities
- Don't rubber-stamp. Quantify problems. Push back on real issues.
